REASONS OF FEDERAL MAGISTRATES COURT The learned Federal Magistrate noted that in SZKJT's application to the Federal Magistrates Court made on 20 March 2007, SZKJT put forward the following grounds:
There was an error of law in the Tribunal's decision constituting a jurisdictional error;
There was procedural error in the Tribunal's decision constituting an absence of natural justice.
